This paper discusses the limitations of stylometry in detecting machine-generated fake news, which falls under the category of natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the potential misuse of neural language models, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the detection of misinformation, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) or cybercrime (cs.CY).
